    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>How Black Comedy Got the Last Laugh</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tanya Ehrmann letter notes Lynn Hirschberg's September 3 article omitted black comedian Chris Rock; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Lynn Hirschberg's cover article (Sept. 3) was missing something: Chris Rock. (There was only a brief interview with Rock, one of the most politically astute and provocative comedians of his generation.) Chris Tucker may demonstrate how to get ahead in show business, but Chris Rock's humor and insight about relationships among and within the races places him solidly in the pantheon of black comedians.</p>
        <p>Tanya Ehrmann  Washington</p>
      </block>
